\boxed{\text{molecular weight (or molar mass)}}

In a Zimm plot, extrapolating to **θ = 0** (the Flory–Huggins θ-solvent condition) yields the **unperturbed molecular weight** of the polymer. The second virial coefficient (*B*) is obtained from the slope of the plot, while the intercept directly relates to the **molecular weight** of the polymer. This method is fundamental in light scattering studies for polymer characterization.
